==English==

{{rank|special|memory|proved|937|plan|pain|official|loss}}

===Noun===
'''plan'''  (''plural:'' [[plans]])
# a [[drawing]] showing technical details of a [[building]], [[machine]], etc., with unwanted details omitted, and often using symbols rather than detailed drawing to represent [[door]]s, [[valve]]s, etc.
# a set of [[intend]]ed actions, through which one expects to achieve a [[goal]].
#A 2-[[dimension]]al drawing of a building as seen from above with obscuring or irrelevant details such as [[roof]] removed, or of a [[floor]] of a building, revealing the internal layout; as distinct from the [[elevation]](7).
====Related words====
(3) [[blueprint]]
====Translations====
*[[Arabic]]: [[خطة]]
*Dutch: plan ''n'' (1), [[ontwerp]] ''n'' (2)
*German: [[Grundriss]] ''m'' (1, of buildings), [[Schema]] ''n'' (1), [[Plan]] ''m'' (1, 2)
*[[Ido]]: [[projeto]], [[programo]]
*Portuguese: planta (1), plano (2)
*Swahili: [[mpango]], [[mipango]] ''pl (noun 3/4)'' (1,2)
*Swedish: plan (2)

===Transitive verb===
'''to plan'''  ([[plans]], [[planned]], [[planning]])
# to [[design]] a building, machine, etc.
# to create a plan for.
# to [[intend]].

====Translations====
